definition.value: The action characteristic of corticotropin-releasing hormone (CRH), any of a number of peptides released by the mammalian hypothalamus into the hypophyseal-portal circulation in response to neural and|or chemical stimuli. Upon receptor binding, CRH increases the rate of corticotropin secretion by the anterior pituitary.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with any peptide with hormonal activity in animals.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with Rho protein, any member of the Rho subfamily of the Ras superfamily of monomeric GTPases. Proteins in the Rho subfamily are involved in relaying signals from cell-surface receptors to the actin cytoskeleton.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the GTP-bound form of the Rho protein.
Catalysis of the reaction -  sphingosine + ATP -eq- sphingosine 1-phosphate + ADP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate + retinol -eq- adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + anhydroretinol.
A protein complex that possesses activity that prevents or downregulates transcription.

A heterodimeric protein complex that can stably associate with TATA-binding protein on promoters, thereby preventing the assembly of transcription factors TFIIA and TFIIB and leading to repression of RNA polymerase II transcription. The two subunits, NC2alpha (Drap1) and NC2beta (Dr1), dimerize through histone fold domains of the H2A|H2B type present in the amino termini.
The action of a molecule that contributes to the structural integrity of the nuclear pore complex.
Catalysis of the reaction -  6-O-phosphono-D-glucono-1,5-lactone + H(2)O -eq- 6-phospho-D-gluconate + H(+).
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a FH1 domain of a protein, a proline-rich domain, usually located in front of a FH2 domain.
An enzyme complex that catalyzes the transfer of a palmitoyl on to serine, forming 3-dehydro-D-sphinganine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  GDP-L-fucose + beta-D-galactosyl-(1,3)-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-R -eq- GDP + beta-D-galactosyl-(1,3)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1,4)]-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-R.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5'-methylthioadenosine + phosphate -eq- adenine + 5-methylthio-D-ribose 1-phosphate.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of a fatty acid amide to yield a fatty acid.

label.value: single-strand selective uracil DNA N-glycosylase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the cleavage of the N-C1' glycosidic bond between the damaged DNA base and the deoxyribose sugar, releasing a free base and leaving an apyrimidinic (AP) site. Enzymes with this activity recognize and remove uracil bases present in single-stranded DNA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3'-phospho-5'-adenylyl sulfate + L-tyrosine methyl ester -eq- L-tyrosine methyl ester 4-sulfate + adenosine 3',5'-diphosphate + H(+).
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a small nuclear RNA (snRNA).
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the U6 small nuclear RNA (U6 snRNA).

label.value: intracellular cyclic nucleotide activated cation channel complex

definition.value: A protein complex that forms a transmembrane channel through which cations ions may pass in response to an intracellular cyclic nucleotide binding to the channel complex or one of its constituent parts.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the SNAP receptor syntaxin-1.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with purine nucleotides, any compound consisting of a purine nucleoside esterified with (ortho)phosphate.

Catalysis of the transfer of protons from mitochondrial intermembrane space into mitochondrial matrix, dissipating the proton gradient across the mitochondrial inner membrane established by the electron transport chain during the oxidative phosphorylation (proton leak). Proton leak uncouples the processes of electron transport|proton generation and ATP synthesis.
Modulates the activity of a sodium channel.
Modulates the activity of a chloride channel.

Combining with a mineralocorticoid and transmitting the signal to the transcriptional machinery by interacting selectively and non-covalently with a specific DNA sequence in order to modulate transcription by RNA polymerase II.
Catalysis of the reaction -  GDP-beta-L-fucose + beta-D-galactosyl-(1,4)-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-R -eq- GDP + 1,4-beta-D-galactosyl-(1,4)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1,4)]-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-R.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-glutamate + ATP + NADPH -eq- ADP + L-glutamate gamma-semialdehyde + NADP+ + phosphate.

A protein complex that catalyzes the reaction 3-methyl-2-oxobutanoate + lipoamide -eq- S-(2-methylpropanoyl)-dihydrolipoamide + carbon dioxide (CO2). This requires thiamine diphosphate -  the enzyme also acts on (S)-3-methyl-2-oxopentanoate and 4-methyl-2-oxo-pentanoate.

A protein complex that consists of a catalytic alpha subunit (alpha-MPP) and a regulatory beta subunit (beta-MPP), and catalyzes the release of N-terminal targeting peptides from precursor proteins imported into the mitochondrion.

Enables the directed movement of glycolipids, compounds containing (usually) 1-4 linked monosaccharide residues joined by a glycosyl linkage to a lipid, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells.

A protein complex that is located in the cell membrane, and is involved in the metabolism of peptides, including neuropeptides. The complex has metalloendopeptidase activity that catalyzes the hydrolysis of protein and peptide substrates, preferentially on carboxyl side of hydrophobic residues.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a region of RNA containing frequent adenine and uridine bases.

Catalysis of the reaction -  3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate + heparan sulfate -eq- adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + heparan sulfate 6-O-sulfate -  results in 6-O-sulfation of glucosamine residues in heparan sulfate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + N-acetylserotonin -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + melatonin. Melatonin is also known as N-acetyl-5-methoxytryptamine.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the sulfonylurea receptor, a regulatory subunit of the ATP-sensitive potassium ion channel.

Catalysis of the reaction -  acyl-CoA + acceptor -eq- 2,3-dehydroacyl-CoA + reduced acceptor, where the acyl group is a very long chain fatty acid residue. A very long-chain fatty acid is a fatty acid which has a chain length greater than C22.

A multienzyme complex found in all multicellular eukaryotes composed of eight proteins with aminoacyl-tRNA synthetase activities (abbreviated as -  ArgRS, AspRS, GluProRS, GlnRS, IleRS, LeuRS, LysRS, MetRS where RS is the enzyme, preceded by the amino acid it uses as a substrate) as well as three non-synthetase proteins (p43, p38, and p18) with diverse functions. Several of these subunits are known dimers, so the total polypeptide count in the multisynthetase complex is at least fifteen. All of the enzymes in this assembly catalyze the same reaction, the covalent attachment of an amino acid to either the 2'- or 3'-hydroxyl of the 3'-terminal adenosine of tRNA, but using different substrates.
A complex consisting of methionyl- and glutamyl-tRNA synthetases. The tRNA synthetases present in the complex bind to their cognate tRNAs more efficiently than they do as monomers.
Catalysis of the reaction -  alpha-D-galactose 1-phosphate + UTP -eq- diphosphate + UDP-D-galactose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acyl-CoA + reduced acceptor + O2 -eq- delta11-acyl-CoA + acceptor + 2 H2O.
The binding activity of a molecule that brings together an anion exchanger and one or more other molecules, permitting them to function in a coordinated way.
Catalysis of the cleavage of a 5' flap structure in DNA, but not other DNA structures -  processes the 5' ends of Okazaki fragments in lagging strand DNA synthesis.
An enzyme complex that catalyzes the ligation of glutamate to cysteine, forming glutamylcysteine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  a nucleoside diphosphate + H2O -eq- a nucleotide + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  a nucleoside triphosphate + H2O -eq- nucleoside diphosphate + phosphate.

Stimulates the exchange of guanyl nucleotides associated with a GTPase of the Rab family. Under normal cellular physiological conditions, the concentration of GTP is higher than that of GDP, favoring the replacement of GDP by GTP in association with the GTPase.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5,6-dihydrouracil + NADP+ -eq- uracil + NADPH + H+.

label.value: single-stranded DNA-dependent ATP-dependent DNA helicase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + H2O -eq- ADP + phosphate, in the presence of single-stranded DNA -  drives the unwinding of a DNA helix.

label.value: single-stranded DNA-dependent ATP-dependent DNA helicase complex

definition.value: A protein complex that possesses single-stranded DNA-dependent DNA helicase activity.
